<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Personality Result</title>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Roboto:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
</head>
  <% if (profileType==='analytical' ) {%>
  <style>
    .conceptualProfile,
    .directiveProfile,
    .behavioralProfile{ opacity: 0.3;}</style>
    <% } else if (profileType==='conceptual' ) {%>
  <style>
    .analyticProfile,
    .directiveProfile,
    .behavioralProfile{opacity: 0.3;}</style>
    <% } else if (profileType==='directive' ) {%>
  <style>
    .analyticProfile,
    .conceptualProfile,
    .behavioralProfile{opacity: 0.3;}</style>
    <% } else { %>
  <style>
    .analyticProfile,
    .conceptualProfile,
    .directiveProfile{opacity: 0.3;}</style>
  <% }; %>
<body class="bodyResults">
  <div class="results">
    <h1>Your result is</h1>
    <div class="profileContainer">
      <div class="analyticProfile">
        <h2>Analytical profile <span class="icon">üìä</span></h2>
        <p>The analytical decision-making style is characterized by a strong commitment to finding the best possible
          answer. Individuals with this style enjoy solving complex problems and feel comfortable handling large
          amounts of information and data. They are innovative, always seeking new approaches and ideas. They like
          to be in control of situations and do not hesitate to take the necessary time to evaluate all available
          options, ensuring that the final decision is the most suitable. Additionally, they appreciate variety
          and new challenges, seeing them as opportunities for growth and learning.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="conceptualProfile">
        <h2>Conceptual profile <span class="icon">üí°</span></h2>
        <p>People with a conceptual decision-making style are achievement-oriented and have a strong inclination
          towards creativity. They feel comfortable exploring hypothetical scenarios and consider various possibilities
          ("what if") before making a decision. Generally, they have a broad and open outlook, allowing them to be
          innovative and think outside the box. Moreover, they take a humanitarian approach, caring about the impact of
          their
          decisions on others. They think long-term and are always focused on the future, enjoying the creation
          and development of new ideas that can bring lasting benefits.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="directiveProfile">
        <h2>Directive profile <span class="icon">üèÜ</span></h2>
        <p>The directive decision-making style is defined by a strong focus on results. Individuals with this style
          primarily rely on established rules and processes to guide their decisions. They tend to be assertive
          and decisive, preferring to make quick decisions and act swiftly without dwelling on unnecessary details.
          They have an intuitive nature that allows them to react quickly to situations. They are strong verbal
          communicators, capable of conveying their decisions clearly and directly, keeping everyone informed
          about the actions being taken.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="behavioralProfile">
        <h2>Behavioral profile <span class="icon">ü§ù</span></h2>
        <p>People with a behavioral decision-making style are very collaborative and work well in teams. They have an
          empathetic nature, understanding and sharing the feelings of others. Before making decisions, they seek the
          opinions and feedback of others, ensuring all stakeholders are heard. They gather relevant information, basing
          their decisions on social intuitions and reading people. Persuasive and effective communicators, they use
          their interpersonal skills to mobilize others around their ideas and decisions.</p>

      </div>
    </div>
    <a class="nextButton" href="/me">Next</a>
  </div>
</body>

</html>